Protocol.text: U937 cells were maintained in RPMI 1640 with 10% (v/v) FCS, 100 U/ml, penicillin, and 100 ug/ml streptomycin at 37°C in a 5% CO2 environment. Actively growing cells from flasks (Nunc) were harvested by centrifugation at 1000 x g for 5 min and washed with PBS or HBSS (Flow Laboratories) before experiments.

Cell cross-linking: Use 5x107 - 1x108 cells (70-80% confluency for adhesion cells of 8-12 15 cm2 plates or 175 cm2 flasks) for each location analysis reaction.
1. Add 1/10 volume of fresh 11% formaldehyde solution to plates.
2. Swirl plates briefly and let them sit at RT for 10 min.
3. Add 1/20 volume of 2.5 M glycine to plates to quench formaldehyde.
4. Rinse cells twice with 5 ml 1X PBS. Harvest cells using silicon scraper.
5. Spin cells at 4k for 10 min at 4°C.6. Transfer cells to 15ml conical tubes and spin 4k 10 min at 4°C.
7. Flash freeze cells in liquid nitrogen and store pellets at -80 °C.

1. Wash 100 ul Dynal magnetic beads (per reaction) in 1 ml fresh block solution.
2.Collect the beads by spinning at 3000 RPM for 3 minutes.
3. Wash beads in 1.5 ml block soln two more times, collect the beads with the magnet.
4. Resuspend beads in 250 ul block soln and add 6-10 ug of Ab.
5.Incubate overnight on a rotating platform at 4°C.
6. Wash beads 3 times in 1 ml block soln.
7. Resuspend in 100 ul block soln.
8. Add 100 ul antibody/magnetic bead mix from step III to IP solution in 15 ml tubes.
9. Rock 4°C O/N

Experiment.name: Genome-wide MLL1 occupancy reveals global and Hox specific transcriptional roles

Description.text: An experiment was performed to understand its role in cell type specification, we have determined the human genomic binding sites of MLL1. MLL1 localizes with Pol II to the 5' end of actively transcribed genes, where histone H3 lysine 4 (H3-K4) trimethylation occurs. The ability of MLL1 to serve as a start site-specific global transcriptional regulator and to participate in larger chromatin domains at the Hox genes reveals the dual roles MLL1 plays in maintenance of cellular identity.
